# Excalibrr Component Rules for Claude Code

## CRITICAL: Always Follow These Rules

### 1. NO INLINE STYLES
- NEVER use `style={{...}}` on any Excalibrr component
- Use component props instead (spacing, theme, variant, etc.)
- If custom styling is absolutely needed, use className with CSS

### 2. Component-Specific Rules

#### Layout (Horizontal, Vertical)
- spacing: "sm" | "md" | "lg" (not gap or margin styles)
- align: for alignment (not justifyContent/alignItems styles)

#### Typography (Texto)
- variant: "h1" | "h2" | "h3" | "body1" | "body2" | "caption"
- color: theme colors (not hex/rgb values)
- weight: "normal" | "medium" | "bold"

#### Buttons (GraviButton)
- theme: "success" | "theme1" | "danger" | "default"
- size: "small" | "medium" | "large"
- Never use backgroundColor, padding, etc.

#### Grids (GraviGrid)
- Configure via columnDefs, not styles
- Use cellClass not cellStyle for styling
- Use custom cell editors: NumberCellEditor, SelectCellEditor

#### Forms
- Wrap in <Form> component
- Use Vertical/Horizontal for layout
- GraviButton for actions

### 3. Before Any Code Generation
1. Read DESIGN_SYSTEM_RULES.md if unsure
2. Check component documentation via excalibrr:get_component
3. Use excalibrr:search_components to find right component

### 4. After Making Changes
- Run excalibrr:cleanup_styles to fix violations automatically

### 5. When Working with Figma
- Use figma-excalibrr-mapper agent for design translation
- Map Figma properties to Excalibrr props, not CSS

## Quick Reference
- Spacing: Use spacing prop or utility classes (mt-4, mb-2)
- Colors: Use theme colors via props
- Flex: Use Horizontal/Vertical components
- Typography: Use Texto with variant prop
- Forms: Use Form component with Vertical layout
